com.adobe.aem.commons.assetshare.search.results

Interface Results

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResultsWrapper

    @ProviderType
public interface Results
    Interface that describes a result set; This is a common interface for results from any search provider.

    • Method Detail

      • getResults

        List<Result> getResults()
        Returns:
        a list of results.

      • getSize

        long getSize()
        Returns:
        the number of results in this results object (equivalent of `getResults().size()`)

      • getTotal

        long getTotal()
        Returns:
        the total number of results for the search. This will be greater than or equal to getSize(). This may be a guess as well.

      • isMore

        boolean isMore()
        Returns:
        true if there are more results. false if there are no more results.

      • getTimeTaken

        long getTimeTaken()
        Returns:
        the time taken to execute this search in milliseconds.

      • getRunningTotal

        long getRunningTotal()
        Returns:
        the number of results returned so far; this is computed using offsets and limits.

      • getNextOffset

        long getNextOffset()
        Returns:
        the next offset if the client would like to load more.

      • getStatus

        Results.Status getStatus()
        Returns:
        the status of the search (Success or Error)

      • getAdditionalData

        org.apache.sling.api.resource.ValueMap getAdditionalData()
        This method acts as a flexible extension point to expose additional data. Note: the returning ValueMap supports modifying operations (ie. put, putAll).
        Returns:
        a ValueMap (optionally) populated with additional data by applications implementing Asset Share Commons.
